<size=20>Get parameter to use for tracking detection</size>
 
I used three different blendshapes combined to check if any of them are changing.

Change the black nodes out to something else if you want to use different parameters for this.

- The three values are added together to use as a single value
- Multiply by 10 to magnify smaller motions.

<size=20>Store last few values in array</size>
Create a Text Array to continuously store the last few rotations.
- Keep the size of the array to 3 by checking the size and continuously removing the top value, so the array only has the last few recent rotations.

<size=20>Take the SUM of array</size>
- Get the values from the array into individual parameters
- Convert the Text Parameters to Numeric Parameters
- Add the first two values, then add the second

<size=20>Calculate the MEAN of array</size>
- just divide the sum by the number of values we added together

Calculate the VARIANCE

VAR = SUM(xi - X)^2/(n-1)
where:
xi - each value of array
X - average of array
n - length of array

<size=20>Send TrackingLost Trigger</size>
If Variance drops below Sensitivity, then send a signal to TrackingLost trigger.

If Variance goes back above Sensitivty, then send a signal to TrackingFound trigger.

These signals will only occur once per state change.
The "TrackingLostFlag" prevents these signals from repeatedly going off.

Tracking Lost Detection by Lunazera ▼——————————————— ▼ Sends Trigger signals to TrackingLost and TrackingFound whenever face tracking is lost or found. Should work with webcam or ARKit tracking. Triggers after roughly 3 seconds. You can use Trigger nodes in other graphs (exampled below) where you need to use these signals! TrackDetectTimer - Timer between each check for blendshape values. Lowering this will make the detection trigger faster (though make it more noisy). Sensitivity - Minimum variance for Tracking Lost to be triggered TrackingLostTimeout - Time in ms after tracking is lost until tracking can be detected again. Dec 29 2023
